- I meant what I said
that night.

13:50.420 --> 13:52.360
I love you.

13:52.560 --> 13:53.870
And I'm sorry.

13:55.960 --> 13:58.490
- So what are you going
to do about it?

13:58.690 --> 13:59.890
Besides being sorry?

14:00.090 --> 14:01.450
- I--I don't know.
What else do you want me to do?

14:01.650 --> 14:03.060
- I want you
to tell everyone you lied.

14:03.260 --> 14:07.760
The guys, the girls,
my parents, Stanford.

14:07.960 --> 14:09.110
I want you to be the one
to be worried

14:09.310 --> 14:10.720
that you won't get
into college now.

14:10.920 --> 14:12.900
I want you to tell everyone

14:13.100 --> 14:15.370
that you're not
the good guy here.

14:20.640 --> 14:23.390
If you won't do it...

14:23.590 --> 14:25.080
maybe I will.

14:28.990 --> 14:30.470
[sighs]

14:37.350 --> 14:38.230
- [bombastic patriotic music]
- Future voters...

14:38.430 --> 14:41.100
I'm here
to tell you the truth

14:41.300 --> 14:43.760
about what transpired
between myself

14:43.960 --> 14:46.890
and my opponent, Buddy Aldrich.

14:47.090 --> 14:48.890
We did not go all the way.
[scoffs]

14:49.090 --> 14:50.370
He lied.

14:50.570 --> 14:55.250
To his friends, to me,
and to you.

14:55.450 --> 14:59.730
Now, does that sound
like a good guy?

14:59.930 --> 15:02.860
- Ugh.
So shrill.

15:03.060 --> 15:04.950
It felt like
I was being scolded.

15:05.150 --> 15:06.430
She sounds jealous.

15:06.630 --> 15:08.300
- Uh, Jane, can you repeat
what you said?

15:08.500 --> 15:10.830
I was thinking about the
last time I saw your bottom.

15:11.030 --> 15:13.350
[all snicker]

15:13.550 --> 15:15.480
I liked it.

15:15.680 --> 15:16.750
But I don't vote.

15:16.950 --> 15:18.970
[groans]

15:19.170 --> 15:21.840
Okay,
so that's not going to work.

15:22.040 --> 15:22.880
What else you got?

15:23.080 --> 15:24.360
- I've got something--

15:24.560 --> 15:26.100
new jacket ideas.

15:26.300 --> 15:29.890
Okay, first up,
the Red Cherries.

15:30.090 --> 15:31.330
We may look sweet,

15:31.530 --> 15:34.190
but if you tick us off,
we get real sour.

15:34.890 --> 15:35.810
Hmm.

15:36.010 --> 15:36.810
You hate it.

15:37.010 --> 15:38.120
[softly] Mm.

15:38.310 --> 15:42.640
- Or the Yellow Jackets
because we wear yellow--

15:42.840 --> 15:43.770
I hate it.

15:43.970 --> 15:45.820
Okay, mm-mm.

15:46.020 --> 15:48.210
- The Pink Fla--
- No pink.

15:48.410 --> 15:49.820
Draw the line at pink.

15:50.020 --> 15:52.220
- [sighs] Nancy, can we put
a pin in the jackets for now?

15:52.420 --> 15:53.960
We need a plan to expose Buddy.

15:54.160 --> 15:57.310
- Buddy's a boy.
Boys are disgusting.

15:57.510 --> 15:59.310
I'm sure he's got something
gross stashed somewhere.

15:59.510 --> 16:01.570
- Every boy in the school's
got a nudie mag in his locker.

16:01.770 --> 16:03.530
- And there may be other
skeletons in his closet.

16:03.730 --> 16:06.230
I know the student records
in Miss McGee's office.

16:06.430 --> 16:08.540
I'll see if there's anything
on there to make him look bad.

16:08.740 --> 16:14.410
- And I'll go undercover into
the belly of the boy beast.

16:14.610 --> 16:15.850
Locker room.

16:16.050 --> 16:17.590
That's where they brag
about all their gross stuff.

16:17.790 --> 16:19.110
If all else fails,

16:19.310 --> 16:21.160
I'll slip some castor oil
in his milk at lunch

16:21.360 --> 16:23.290
and make him caca
in his khakis!

16:23.490 --> 16:25.730
[laughs]
You can't come back from that!

16:25.930 --> 16:26.950
I don't care who you are.

16:27.150 --> 16:28.500
[laughs]

16:31.770 --> 16:32.690
Is this thing on?

16:32.890 --> 16:34.210
Nancy, feet off the desk.

16:34.410 --> 16:36.300
Olivia, lose the gum.

16:36.500 --> 16:38.730
And you two, stop slouching.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.350
Swizzle wizzle!

16:42.550 --> 16:45.310
- Come on, bro.
[metallic clanking]

16:45.510 --> 16:48.440
- [laughter]
- [sighs]

16:50.220 --> 16:52.890
- How are we going
to get past McGee?

16:53.090 --> 16:54.620
Allow me.

16:59.010 --> 17:00.200
Miss McGee?

17:00.400 --> 17:03.160
I don't feel so good!
[groans]

17:03.360 --> 17:04.510
Where does it hurt, dear?

17:04.710 --> 17:07.380
- [groaning] Everywhere!
I ate some old bologna.

17:07.580 --> 17:09.990
I'm gonna caca in my khakis!

17:10.190 --> 17:11.160
[laughter]

17:11.360 --> 17:12.380
Come along.

17:12.580 --> 17:14.430
I'm taking you to
the nurse's office.

17:14.630 --> 17:17.130
Remain seated until
that detention bell rings.

17:17.330 --> 17:18.220
- [groaning]
- Understood?

17:18.410 --> 17:19.870
- All right. Okay.
- [groans]

17:20.070 --> 17:23.000
[energetic rock music]

17:23.200 --> 17:25.000
[groaning]

17:25.200 --> 17:27.220
- Dear, Nurse Penelope's
left for the day.

17:27.420 --> 17:28.970
I don't know what to do.

17:29.160 --> 17:36.180
♪

17:37.270 --> 17:39.020
[softly] Good.

17:39.220 --> 17:46.230
♪

17:49.670 --> 17:50.990
Ugh.

17:51.190 --> 17:58.200
♪

18:21.970 --> 18:23.620
[music stops]

18:24.920 --> 18:25.840
[door opens]

18:37.460 --> 18:39.910
- Hey.
- [gasps]

18:40.100 --> 18:41.340
You want a key?

18:41.540 --> 18:43.260
[chuckles softly]

18:43.460 --> 18:44.950
That'd be nice.

18:45.150 --> 18:47.910
[suspenseful music]

18:48.110 --> 18:49.130
♪

18:49.330 --> 18:50.740
[hinges creak]

18:50.940 --> 18:56.970
♪

18:57.170 --> 18:59.010
Ew.

18:59.210 --> 19:00.190
Gross.

19:00.390 --> 19:03.970
♪

19:04.170 --> 19:05.100
[door closes]

19:05.300 --> 19:08.720
[indistinct chatter]

19:08.920 --> 19:10.460
Just admit it, Buddy.

19:10.660 --> 19:14.640
Admit what you did
to everybody here.

19:14.840 --> 19:16.250
Okay.

19:16.450 --> 19:18.290
♪

19:18.490 --> 19:20.990
I cut the cheese.
[laughter]

19:21.190 --> 19:22.560
- What a stand-up guy.

19:22.760 --> 19:24.690
I haven't copped to a ripper
since third grade.

19:24.890 --> 19:26.560
- You haven't copped a feel
since you were breastfeeding.

19:26.760 --> 19:27.470
[laughter]

19:27.670 --> 19:29.740
Speaking of copping a feel,

19:29.940 --> 19:31.700
you candy asses going
to Dot's party tonight,

19:31.900 --> 19:32.870
or am I going to have to

19:33.070 --> 19:34.090
neck the whole
cheerleading team myself?

19:34.290 --> 19:35.270
[laughter]

19:35.460 --> 19:36.830
- Just keep your distance
from Rosemary.

19:37.030 --> 19:38.960
She said I might get
to second base tonight.

19:39.160 --> 19:40.660
[laughter and exclamations]

19:40.860 --> 19:41.790
- Are you going to the
party tonight, Buddy?

19:41.990 --> 19:43.840
- Yeah, I guess so.
Susan asked me.

19:44.040 --> 19:47.150
- You mean Fort Knox?
You should bring Jane instead.

19:47.350 --> 19:49.240
I hear Dot's house
has seven bedrooms.

19:49.440 --> 19:51.850
[all howl]

19:52.050 --> 19:54.240
I got to take a shower.

19:54.440 --> 19:56.370
Hey, I got a question.

19:56.570 --> 19:58.200
Are lemons and limes
the same fruit?

19:58.400 --> 20:01.030
Like, is a lemon sort
of a ripe lime?

20:01.230 --> 20:02.250
- [laughing]
What? No.

20:02.450 --> 20:04.990
They're two separate fruits.

20:05.190 --> 20:06.170
Right?

20:06.370 --> 20:07.650
Wait.

20:07.840 --> 20:10.210
So is a cantaloupe
just a ripe honeydew?

20:10.410 --> 20:11.610
[suspenseful music]

20:11.810 --> 20:14.220
- Where are we going?
- Trust me.

20:14.420 --> 20:16.740
- Just so you know, I don't
normally do things like this.

20:16.940 --> 20:18.830
- [chuckles]
Sure you don't.

20:19.030 --> 20:20.140
I'm serious.

20:20.340 --> 20:21.400
If you say so.

20:21.600 --> 20:22.880
- The only reason
I'm doing this

20:23.080 --> 20:25.180
is because I want people
to know the truth about Buddy.

20:25.380 --> 20:26.880
- Mm.
- This is a one-time thing.

20:27.080 --> 20:28.230
Yeah, sure.

20:28.430 --> 20:29.840
One-time thing,

20:30.040 --> 20:32.240
like flashing your ass
at an assembly, for example.

20:32.430 --> 20:35.890
♪

20:36.090 --> 20:37.240
- Wait.
What are we doing in here?

20:37.440 --> 20:38.330
Are you trying
to get us in trouble?

20:38.530 --> 20:39.630
You said you wanted a key.

20:39.830 --> 20:40.850
- Yes, but this is
not--it's not--

20:41.050 --> 20:42.290
Come on.

20:42.490 --> 20:49.590
♪

20:51.250 --> 20:52.430
Hold on, Cynthia.

20:52.630 --> 20:54.470
Let me get something
from my office.

20:54.670 --> 20:55.820
[upbeat notes]

20:56.020 --> 20:57.220
Bingo.

20:57.420 --> 20:59.220
[whistling]

20:59.420 --> 21:01.660
[tense music]

21:01.860 --> 21:03.220
♪ Shine those shoes

21:03.420 --> 21:06.050
♪ Before you say
that you love me ♪

21:06.250 --> 21:07.440
[chuckles]

21:07.640 --> 21:10.010
[scatting cheerfully]

21:10.210 --> 21:11.840
[moaning softly]

21:12.040 --> 21:15.370
Ah! [exhales deeply]

21:15.560 --> 21:16.930
The ballpark has come alive.

21:17.130 --> 21:19.150
Tensions are high between
the Dodgers and the Giants.

21:19.350 --> 21:21.800
Dodgers are first up to bat,
putting Robinson in to--

21:27.850 --> 21:31.420
- Did you tell the principal
I tried to seduce you?

21:31.620 --> 21:33.340
[sighs softly]

21:33.540 --> 21:34.860
I had to.

21:35.060 --> 21:36.260
My job was at stake.

21:36.460 --> 21:39.390
- I was locked in my room
all summer.

21:39.590 --> 21:40.690
I can't take Honors English

21:40.890 --> 21:41.910
because you're the only one
who teaches it.

21:42.110 --> 21:44.390
I thought you almost
lost your job,

21:44.590 --> 21:45.530
but really,
you just hung me out to dry

21:45.730 --> 21:46.870
to save your own skin.

21:47.070 --> 21:49.310
I didn't lie.

21:49.510 --> 21:50.400
Excuse me?

21:50.600 --> 21:52.270
Sometimes students

21:52.470 --> 21:57.970
can misconstrue a teacher's
interests as something more.

21:58.170 --> 21:59.710
What?

21:59.910 --> 22:01.720
You asked me
to stay after class.

22:01.920 --> 22:04.240
You gave me books, poetry.

22:04.440 --> 22:07.320
- All things a teacher does to
encourage a promising student.

22:10.540 --> 22:12.510
- You can't just pretend
this didn't happen.

22:12.710 --> 22:16.210
- I'm sure that you'll find
someone your own age

22:16.410 --> 22:18.460
who finds you special
in that way.

22:20.940 --> 22:23.340
But I think
you should leave now.

22:24.120 --> 22:26.960
[soft dramatic music]

22:27.160 --> 22:29.480
♪

22:29.680 --> 22:30.960
[clears throat]

22:31.160 --> 22:35.790
♪

22:35.990 --> 22:37.880
- The Giants
have Gómez pitching.

22:38.080 --> 22:40.930
First pitch, foul ball
off the end of the bat.

22:41.130 --> 22:42.190
[chuckles]

22:42.390 --> 22:43.710
- Second pitch,
ball outside and it hits.

22:43.910 --> 22:46.850
- Come on, come on. Come on!
- What a beautiful drive!

22:47.050 --> 22:48.110
[phone ringing]
There goes Taylor.

22:48.310 --> 22:50.110
Goes way back
towards the wall!

22:50.310 --> 22:51.800
[radio switches off]

22:53.110 --> 22:54.900
Hello?

22:55.100 --> 22:56.940
Superintendent Fletcher.
[chuckles]

22:57.140 --> 22:59.380
- [inaudible]
- Of course. I'm sorry.

22:59.580 --> 23:00.910
My assistant principal
appears to have

23:01.100 --> 23:04.210
misplaced those budgets,
which I finished ages ago.

23:04.410 --> 23:05.210
Can I call you back?

23:05.410 --> 23:06.690
[soft dramatic music]

23:06.890 --> 23:08.170
Great.
[receiver clicks]

23:08.370 --> 23:09.830
Miss McGee!

23:10.030 --> 23:12.350
♪

23:12.550 --> 23:13.740
[door shuts]

23:13.940 --> 23:15.490
♪

23:15.680 --> 23:17.310
- [keys jangling]
- Got what we came for.

23:17.510 --> 23:19.920
[chuckles softly]
Let's go.

23:20.120 --> 23:21.320
[groaning]

23:21.520 --> 23:24.230
- Is it a shooting
or stabbing pain?

23:24.430 --> 23:25.360
What's the difference?

23:25.560 --> 23:27.320
- One's bad.
- [groaning]

23:27.520 --> 23:30.460
And the other is also bad.

23:30.660 --> 23:32.150
Oh, for heaven's sakes!

23:32.350 --> 23:34.230
[bell rings]

23:36.150 --> 23:39.420
- I'm suddenly
feeling much better.

23:39.620 --> 23:41.420
Are you sure?

23:41.620 --> 23:42.690
Yeah.

23:42.890 --> 23:45.080
It's all your ace nursing,
Miss McGee.

23:45.280 --> 23:47.430
Hey, see you tomorrow
in detention.

23:47.630 --> 23:49.260
And the next day...
[exhales deeply]

23:49.460 --> 23:52.520
And the next day
and the next day.

23:52.720 --> 23:55.480
[soft upbeat rock music]

23:55.680 --> 24:02.740
♪

24:10.270 --> 24:11.580
[shudders]

24:11.780 --> 24:18.840
♪

24:22.670 --> 24:24.080
It's not working.

24:24.270 --> 24:27.950
- Well, these might
be the classroom keys.

24:28.150 --> 24:30.510
- So I did all of
that for nothing.

24:33.900 --> 24:36.910
[soft dramatic music]

24:37.110 --> 24:44.000
♪

24:52.830 --> 24:55.450
- [chuckles]
Wow.

24:55.650 --> 24:57.240
Where'd you learn that?

24:57.440 --> 24:59.680
Jail.

24:59.880 --> 25:01.500
I'm teasing.
[chuckles]

25:01.700 --> 25:02.770
[gasps softly]

25:02.970 --> 25:04.760
- Saw it in a movie.
- [chuckles softly]

25:06.410 --> 25:08.770
No Marilyn, no Jane Russell,

25:08.970 --> 25:11.120
but he's got a picture
of this guy?

25:11.320 --> 25:16.170
- His volunteer schedule
for the soup kitchen...

25:16.370 --> 25:18.260
birthday card from grandma.

25:18.460 --> 25:19.610
Oh, library book.

25:19.810 --> 25:21.780
It's not even overdue.

25:24.520 --> 25:29.040
It's addressed to you.

25:35.440 --> 25:36.320
You're welcome.

25:36.520 --> 25:37.710
Yeah. Thanks.

25:43.360 --> 25:46.240
[mischievous jazz music]

25:46.440 --> 25:50.680
♪

25:50.880 --> 25:52.120
It's overdue now.

25:52.320 --> 25:54.080
[indistinct chatter]

25:54.280 --> 25:55.510
♪

25:55.710 --> 25:58.690
- "Jane, I've always thought
of myself as a good guy,

25:58.890 --> 26:01.520
"but after what you said,
I realized I'm not.

26:01.720 --> 26:03.300
"I've done loads
of terrible things.

26:03.500 --> 26:07.090
"I've cheated on tests,
smoked, drank liquor,

26:07.290 --> 26:11.920
and never told anyone this,
but I'm a perverted sex fiend."

26:12.120 --> 26:13.530
[laughter, gasps, and groans]

26:13.730 --> 26:17.320
"I'm addicted to self-abuse,
sometimes four times a day."

26:17.520 --> 26:19.890
- You think all that forearm
work helps him with football?

26:20.090 --> 26:21.280
Mm!

26:21.480 --> 26:22.760
- "I'm sorry I lied about
us going all the way.

26:22.960 --> 26:24.240
"I know that you haven't.

26:24.440 --> 26:29.810
The worst part is that I have,
last year with Susie."

26:30.010 --> 26:31.720
[gasping and retching]

26:31.920 --> 26:33.120
"But I regret that

26:33.320 --> 26:35.510
because I wasn't in love
with her like I--"

26:35.710 --> 26:37.210
then he crossed out "was"
and wrote,

26:37.410 --> 26:39.950
"Am in love with you.

26:40.150 --> 26:42.780
Please forgive me.
Love, Buddy."

26:42.980 --> 26:45.220
This is perfect.

26:45.420 --> 26:46.830
We just got to show
everyone this letter.

26:47.030 --> 26:48.440
- This isn't just
some nudie mag.

26:48.640 --> 26:49.660
That'd be wrong.

26:49.860 --> 26:51.880
- More wrong than
what he did to you?

26:52.070 --> 26:53.920
Come on.
He's asking for it.

26:54.120 --> 26:55.360
- What if we
blackmailed him instead?

26:55.560 --> 26:56.440
- [gasps]
- [chuckles]

26:56.640 --> 26:57.920
Either he drops
out of the race,

26:58.120 --> 27:00.230
or we expose him for the
lying dirtbag he really is.

27:00.430 --> 27:01.800
- The socs are having
their party tonight.

27:02.000 --> 27:02.890
I don't know.

27:03.090 --> 27:04.240
He had the perfect chance

27:04.430 --> 27:06.060
to set the record straight
in the locker room,

27:06.260 --> 27:08.500
but he just left
and went into the shower.

27:08.700 --> 27:10.070
- Yeah, probably
to flog his log.

27:10.270 --> 27:12.240
Oh! No.

27:12.440 --> 27:13.940
- Hey!
- Ew, nasty!

27:14.140 --> 27:16.200
- Oh, I'll get the
T-Birds to drive us.

27:16.400 --> 27:18.200
♪

27:23.160 --> 27:26.300
- Can I tempt anyone
with a salmon mousse canapé?

27:26.500 --> 27:29.650
- [sniffs] Ugh.
Don't you have any real food?

27:29.850 --> 27:31.700
[doo-wop music playing]

27:31.900 --> 27:35.610
- Buddy, oh my gosh.
It's our song.

27:35.810 --> 27:38.140
- I know.
I saw you put the record on.

27:38.340 --> 27:39.400
♪

27:39.600 --> 27:40.620
- ♪ When you...
[door opens loudly]

27:40.820 --> 27:42.220
♪ Are near me

27:43.440 --> 27:47.800
- Who's at the door?
- What's going on?

27:48.000 --> 27:50.540
[rollicking
rock and roll music]

27:50.740 --> 27:52.760
♪

27:52.960 --> 27:54.890
- What?
Am I overdressed?

27:55.090 --> 27:56.500
What are they doing here?

27:56.700 --> 27:59.330
Dot, did you invite them?

27:59.530 --> 28:01.340
We weren't invited.

28:01.540 --> 28:03.640
We're crashing.

28:03.840 --> 28:05.600
- Dot doesn't want
a bunch of gang members

28:05.800 --> 28:06.780
messing up her house.

28:06.980 --> 28:10.210
Hey, we're housebroken.

28:10.410 --> 28:11.740
They can stay.

28:11.940 --> 28:14.700
- ♪ Brought
her whole family too ♪

28:14.900 --> 28:16.350
- ♪ Took off their hats...
- Fine.

28:16.550 --> 28:18.660
♪ Coats, and shoes,
ate up all the food ♪

28:18.860 --> 28:20.140
♪ Then they took a snooze

28:20.340 --> 28:21.970
♪ And they're breakin' up
the house every night ♪

28:22.160 --> 28:23.710
- Uh-uh.
Not so fast.

28:23.910 --> 28:25.660
Shoes off, both of them.

28:25.860 --> 28:29.320
Okay,
house rules, so listen up.

28:29.520 --> 28:31.540
[upbeat jazzy flourish]

28:31.740 --> 28:34.540
Upstairs is off-limits,
but there's my bedroom.

28:34.740 --> 28:38.240
And that's my second bedroom,
where we keep the rabbits.

28:38.440 --> 28:41.250
Oh, one of them went missing,
so watch where you step.

28:41.440 --> 28:44.810
- [chuckling] Jeez.
This place is fat city.

28:45.010 --> 28:47.600
It's real smart.

28:47.800 --> 28:49.650
My parents are super rich.

28:49.840 --> 28:50.910
You know Colonel Candy?

28:51.110 --> 28:52.950
That's my dad, the Colonel.

28:53.150 --> 28:54.650
He says I'm the candy princess.

28:54.850 --> 28:57.390
♪ Oh, honey

28:57.590 --> 28:59.310
That's my dad's study.

28:59.510 --> 29:00.390
Do not go in there.

29:00.590 --> 29:02.480
I have never been in there,
ever.

29:02.680 --> 29:04.400
Okay.

