43:53.440 --> 43:55.590
- Ooh. [chuckles nervously]
It burns.

43:55.790 --> 43:56.810
Tastes like an ashtray.

43:57.010 --> 43:58.070
You can handle it, right?

43:58.270 --> 44:00.420
- Yeah. [chuckles]
Yeah.

44:00.620 --> 44:01.730
Whoo!

44:01.930 --> 44:03.950
- Whoo!
[laughter]

44:04.150 --> 44:06.130
- Another round, boys.
[laughter]

44:06.330 --> 44:08.610
- They fell for it?
- Hook, line, and sinker.

44:08.810 --> 44:09.910
Oh!

44:10.110 --> 44:11.440
- And I filled it
all the way to the top.

44:11.630 --> 44:13.180
[coughing downstairs]

44:13.380 --> 44:15.130
[giggling]

44:17.690 --> 44:18.880
What?

44:19.080 --> 44:21.010
I was a Girl Scout.

44:21.210 --> 44:25.060
- You're something special.
You know that?

44:25.260 --> 44:25.880
[laughter]

44:26.080 --> 44:28.100
[door latch thumping]

44:28.300 --> 44:29.450
Open the door.

44:29.650 --> 44:32.150
- Hey. Let us out of here.
What's the big idea?

44:32.350 --> 44:34.980
- The idea is that you spiked
the punch with alcohol.

44:35.180 --> 44:37.370
- So we spiked your alcohol
with castor oil.

44:37.570 --> 44:38.420
What?

44:38.620 --> 44:39.590
Don't worry.

44:39.790 --> 44:41.420
It is a safe
and effective dose.

44:41.620 --> 44:43.550
It's no big deal!

44:43.750 --> 44:45.120
- Just something
to loosen you up.

44:45.320 --> 44:47.470
- Let us out of here!
This isn't funny!

44:47.670 --> 44:48.910
You're right.

44:49.110 --> 44:50.430
It's not funny to put
something in somebody's drink

44:50.630 --> 44:52.650
that makes them feel
out of control of their body.

44:52.850 --> 44:54.650
- Thank God you snooped
in those medicine cabinets.

44:54.850 --> 44:56.440
Dot's mom has a lot of pills.

44:56.640 --> 44:58.740
Let us out, you pinko tramps!

44:58.940 --> 45:01.220
Do you know who my dad is?

45:01.420 --> 45:04.100
[laughter]

45:04.300 --> 45:06.750
Excellent work, pinko tramps!

45:06.950 --> 45:10.280
- The Pinko Tramps.
Now that is a jacket.

45:10.480 --> 45:11.580
Why not?

45:11.780 --> 45:13.890
Everyone already thinks
we're such bad girls.

45:14.090 --> 45:16.370
- [fancy accent]
We're not girls, we're ladies.

45:16.570 --> 45:17.890
[laughs]

45:18.090 --> 45:19.930
The Pink Ladies.

45:25.460 --> 45:26.510
Fine.

45:26.710 --> 45:28.730
I'll consider it
on a trial basis.

45:28.930 --> 45:30.250
[laughter]

45:30.450 --> 45:33.470
- So Jane, you think a
Pink Lady can become president?

45:33.670 --> 45:35.740
- I've spent so much time
just trying to prove

45:35.940 --> 45:38.830
that I'm the good guy
and Buddy is the bad guy,

45:39.030 --> 45:40.790
but I'm realizing
that maybe sometimes,

45:40.990 --> 45:42.130
you got to be bad to do good.

45:42.330 --> 45:45.140
- That is not
a bad campaign slogan

45:45.340 --> 45:46.700
for the leader of a girl gang.

45:46.900 --> 45:50.260
[gasps and laughs]

45:51.480 --> 45:54.800
- Anyone know for
stopping by the school?

45:55.000 --> 45:56.760
[suspenseful music]

45:56.960 --> 45:57.930
Let's go.

45:58.130 --> 46:05.110
♪

46:08.850 --> 46:12.990
- ♪ School bells,
school bells, ring for me ♪

46:13.190 --> 46:14.910
[rollicking
rock and roll music]

46:15.110 --> 46:17.130
- I've decided that
I have too much to do

46:17.330 --> 46:19.390
without having to keep
an eye on you girls

46:19.590 --> 46:24.090
every day after school,
so no more detention.

46:24.290 --> 46:28.750
You are all still
being punished.

46:28.950 --> 46:33.010
Since you showed such a flair
for the theatrics yesterday,

46:33.210 --> 46:35.010
you're going to join
the thespians

46:35.210 --> 46:38.100
so you can learn
how to act like a lady.

46:38.300 --> 46:39.630
No way.

46:39.830 --> 46:41.060
Those kids have their heads
so far up their own asses,

46:41.260 --> 46:44.070
I'm surprised they
can walk straight.

46:44.270 --> 46:45.980
- Olivia, you seem
to enjoy filing,

46:46.180 --> 46:48.510
so I'm making you
my office assistant.

46:48.700 --> 46:51.640
You can start with those.

46:51.840 --> 46:56.210
Jane, I got reports of you
roaming the halls yesterday,

46:56.410 --> 47:01.390
so I figured I'd better
give you this to do it in.

47:01.590 --> 47:02.870
A hall monitor?

47:03.070 --> 47:04.480
But everybody
in school hates them.

47:04.680 --> 47:05.650
Good luck courting votes

47:05.850 --> 47:08.350
while you're writing
tardy slips.

47:08.550 --> 47:10.750
And you.

47:10.940 --> 47:12.310
Well, I ran out of jobs,

47:12.510 --> 47:14.920
so you will help me out
with whatever I need

47:15.120 --> 47:16.320
whenever I need it.

47:16.520 --> 47:18.450
- Can we start
with a wardrobe makeover?

47:18.650 --> 47:21.540
[stifled snickering]

47:21.740 --> 47:23.270
You're dismissed.

47:27.930 --> 47:29.420
- What you got in there?
A dead body?

47:29.620 --> 47:30.460
No.

47:30.660 --> 47:33.240
Even better.

47:34.540 --> 47:37.460
[indistinct chatter]

47:40.940 --> 47:44.740
- Hey, you don't
have to do that.

47:44.940 --> 47:46.740
- I'm sorry.
They ruined your poster.

47:46.940 --> 47:48.350
- I'm the one
who should be sorry.

47:48.550 --> 47:52.050
I--I heard about what
happened with the punch.

47:52.250 --> 47:53.830
- You must think
I'm a total floozy.

47:54.030 --> 47:56.090
Those guys are jerks.

47:56.290 --> 47:58.230
Not all guys suck.

47:58.430 --> 48:00.310
You're one of the good ones.

48:02.960 --> 48:05.580
Susan...

48:05.780 --> 48:08.240
I'm not looking
for a girlfriend right now,

48:08.440 --> 48:10.590
but...

48:10.790 --> 48:13.760
I do need a campaign manager.

48:13.960 --> 48:15.770
[door opens loudly]

48:15.970 --> 48:18.070
[excited indistinct chatter]

48:18.270 --> 48:21.250
[powerful upbeat music]

48:21.450 --> 48:22.290
♪

48:22.490 --> 48:23.640
Hey!

48:23.840 --> 48:30.480
♪

48:30.680 --> 48:31.830
Hey, dig that!

48:32.030 --> 48:39.090
♪

48:45.700 --> 48:48.670
[slaps echoing,
slow motion shouting]

48:48.870 --> 48:51.020
♪

48:51.220 --> 48:52.670
- [slow motion]
Yeah, and you know what?

48:52.870 --> 48:53.890
[Dot shouting indistinctly]

48:54.090 --> 49:00.930
♪
